## Container/Wrapper/Block Vocabulary

Consistent suffix vocabulary used throughout all templates:

| Suffix | Role | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `.container` | Outermost layout container inside `<section>` | `<div class="container">` |
| `.container.grid` | Grid layout variant | `<div class="container grid">` |
| `.container.grid.grid-2-col` | 2-column grid | `<div class="container grid grid-2-col">` |
| `*-wrapper` | Grouping container for a region | `.media-wrapper`, `.content-wrapper`, `.title-wrapper`, `.carousel-wrapper`, `.badges-wrapper` |
| `*-block` | A self-contained content unit | `.title-block`, `.content-block`, `.media-block`, `.list-block`, `.cta-block`, `.grid-block`, `.faq-block` |
| `*-item` or `*-card` | Repeating unit within a loop | `.review-item`, `.testimonial-item`, `.faq-item`, `.timeline-card`, `.benefits-item`, `.grid-item` |

### Typical Section Structure

```php
<section class="[name] [modifiers]">
    <div class="container [grid-class]">
        <div class="[role]-wrapper">
            <div class="[role]-block">
                <!-- content -->
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="[role]-wrapper">
            <div class="[role]-block">
                <!-- content -->
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
```

