## Carousel Pattern (Actual)

The `.container` child gets both a generic `.carousel` class and a **prefix-specific** class. The JS utility picks it up by prefix.

```php
<div class="wrapper carousel-wrapper carousel [prefix]-carousel">
    <div class="[item-class]">...</div>
</div>
```

Navigation arrows and dots:
```php
<div class="wrapper navigation-wrapper [prefix]-navigation">
    <div class="previous">
        <button type="button" class="[prefix]-prev">
            <img src="...arrow-circle_left.svg" .../>
        </button>
    </div>
    <div class="nav-dots [prefix]-dots">
        <button class="nav-dot active" data-slide="0"></button>
        <button class="nav-dot" data-slide="1"></button>
    </div>
    <div class="next">
        <button type="button" class="[prefix]-next">
            <img src="...arrow-circle_right.svg" .../>
        </button>
    </div>
</div>
```

```javascript
initCarousel({}, '.[prefix]');
```

